title: Cutrine Plus Granulated Algaecide, 30 lbs
features: Rapid sinking granules for targeted delivery to bottom-growing algae
Visible reduction of algae growth 1-2 days
Chelating agents prevent the precipitation of copper with carbonates and bicarbonates in the water for longer activity
Stays active in the water longer than copper sulfate
Ideal for algae in deeper waters or bottom growing algae - use Cutrine Plus Algaecide (liquid) for algae on the surface or in the water column
Cannot be shipped to AK, CT, HI, ME, NJ, NY, WA or Canada. Orders placed from these states will be cancelled.
description: This algaecide helps controls algae before it reaches the surface, making it very effective in reducing surface filamentous and planktonic algae. Ideally suited for bottom growing algae and spot treatments along docks, beaches, boat launches and fishing areas, Cutrine Plus algaecide and herbicide effectively controls a broad range of algae, including green algae, golden algae, cyanobacteria and more. Ensure your water is compatible with these cleaning chemicals before purchasing. No shipping available to CA, CT, ME, NI, NY, OR, or WA. About the Brand: Applied Biochemists was developed for use in lakes, ponds, and other outdoor bodies of water. Our water care products are both economical and powerful enough for the toughest jobs. Within Applied Biochemists’ wide selection of products, we offer everything from algaecides and deposit control formulas to non-chlorine shock treatments, powerful surface cleaners, clarifiers, enzyme-based cleaners, and more.
